WEBVTT

01:28.423 --> 01:30.467
<font color="#D900D9">(CRACKLING AND RUMBLING)</font>

01:40.018 --> 01:41.978
<font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER RUMBLING)</font>

01:42.687 --> 01:44.314
<font color="#D900D9">(BIRDS CHIRPING)</font>

01:47.192 --> 01:49.194
<font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING CONTINUES)</font>

02:15.220 --> 02:17.055
<font color="#D900D9">(JANGLING)</font>

02:30.985 --> 02:32.779
<font color="#D900D9">(FIRE CRACKLING)</font>

02:42.080 --> 02:43.623
Roman, huh?

02:49.337 --> 02:51.506
That's a tribune's ring?

02:55.760 --> 02:56.928
Yes.

03:00.723 --> 03:02.600
Have you come far?

03:07.814 --> 03:09.357
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(VOICE ECHOES)</font>
<i>Legion 10!</i>

03:10.358 --> 03:11.359
Move forward!

03:11.442 --> 03:12.443
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAMORING)</font>

03:13.862 --> 03:15.238
<font color="#808080">CENTURION:</font> Now! Come on!

03:15.321 --> 03:16.447
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

03:19.534 --> 03:20.952
Come on!

03:22.954 --> 03:24.372
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

03:27.458 --> 03:30.378
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> <i>For 30 years,
the Roman Empire of Tiberius Caesar</i>

03:30.461 --> 03:33.381
<i>has ruled the wasteland
of Judaea and its people.</i>

03:33.464 --> 03:36.593
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Barabbas! Barabbas!

03:36.676 --> 03:38.845
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> <i>As tribune
to Prefect Pontius Pilate,</i>

03:38.928 --> 03:42.265
<i>my task is to keep order
in a city that is steeped in unrest.</i>

03:42.348 --> 03:44.100
<font color="#808080">CENTURION:</font> Simple formation!

03:45.476 --> 03:47.645
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> <i>The Jews pray
to their single God, Yahweh,</i>

03:47.729 --> 03:49.814
<i>for the arrival
of the mystical Messiah</i>

03:50.857 --> 03:54.861
<i>as their religious leaders, the Sanhedrin,
try to keep an uneasy peace.</i>

03:54.944 --> 03:58.907
<i>But each day creates more zealots
to challenge the rule of Rome</i>

03:58.990 --> 04:00.700
<i>and bring freedom.</i>

04:00.783 --> 04:02.076
<i>- Instead...</i>
- <font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

04:02.160 --> 04:03.494
<i>...we bring them death.</i>

04:03.661 --> 04:05.663
- <font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>
- Pilum up!

04:08.499 --> 04:10.376
Pilum ranks, launch!

04:11.502 --> 04:12.712
Launch!

04:12.795 --> 04:14.714
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING CONTINUES)</font>

04:16.841 --> 04:18.051
Form up!

04:18.843 --> 04:20.053
Draw!

04:24.015 --> 04:25.516
Testudo!

04:30.188 --> 04:32.065
Hold this line!

04:32.148 --> 04:33.524
Forward!

04:40.156 --> 04:41.324
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

04:50.124 --> 04:51.626
Forward!

04:56.422 --> 04:57.757
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

04:58.383 --> 05:00.051
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAMORING CONTINUES)</font>

05:14.482 --> 05:15.733
<font color="#D900D9">(FIERCE YELLING)</font>

05:21.531 --> 05:23.032
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING CONTINUES)</font>

05:25.910 --> 05:27.245
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN YELLS)</font>

05:27.412 --> 05:30.081
<font color="#808080">CENTURION:</font> Tribune, we have Barabbas!

05:30.707 --> 05:31.749
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

05:32.583 --> 05:33.876
Bring him.

05:34.502 --> 05:36.546
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING AND YELLING)</font>

05:40.008 --> 05:41.342
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

05:41.551 --> 05:42.885
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

05:46.848 --> 05:48.433
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

05:49.767 --> 05:51.269
I know how this ends.

05:51.394 --> 05:54.814
Then tell Yahweh you are coming,
courtesy of Mars.

05:55.023 --> 06:00.111
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font> It must pain you to know that
the one true God chooses us over you.

06:00.570 --> 06:02.363
Not today, he didn't.

06:03.031 --> 06:07.452
When the Messiah comes,
Rome will be nothing!

06:08.953 --> 06:10.455
Until then...

06:10.538 --> 06:11.539
<font color="#D900D9">(BARABBAS GROANS)</font>

06:22.759 --> 06:24.719
<font color="#D900D9">(HORSES NEIGHING)</font>

06:27.430 --> 06:28.639
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN GROANS)</font>

06:29.474 --> 06:30.767
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

06:31.934 --> 06:33.478
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING CONTINUES)</font>

06:38.441 --> 06:39.817
<font color="#D900D9">(HORSE HUFFS)</font>

06:43.112 --> 06:45.156
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING AND PANTING CONTINUES)</font>

06:52.163 --> 06:54.624
Tribune, Pilate summons you.

06:58.169 --> 06:59.921
I'm yet sticky with filth.

07:00.004 --> 07:02.256
No matter. There's more trouble.

07:08.513 --> 07:10.139
<font color="#D900D9">(CART CLATTERING)</font>

07:28.491 --> 07:29.951
Come on, come on!

07:35.456 --> 07:36.707
Did you win?

07:38.626 --> 07:40.294
I was told to hurry.

07:41.462 --> 07:44.048
In truth, you're well dressed for this job.

07:45.049 --> 07:47.885
- What's happened?
- Passover.

07:48.678 --> 07:52.473
Every hothead and holy fool in Judaea
was here, stirring the pot.

07:53.724 --> 07:56.811
Some ascetic won a following
by making waves,

07:56.894 --> 07:59.647
so the Sanhedrin decided to put him down.

07:59.730 --> 08:02.650
They sent a lathered mob here,
screaming for his blood

08:02.733 --> 08:05.570
because he claims to be their Messiah.

08:09.574 --> 08:10.783
<font color="#D900D9">(SLURPS)</font>

08:13.411 --> 08:15.121
I had to crucify him.

08:19.333 --> 08:21.919
Don't give me that look.
I've had enough already.

08:22.003 --> 08:23.171
<font color="#D900D9">(GOBLET CLANKS)</font>

08:23.254 --> 08:26.883
I had a situation, Tribune,
something you don't seem to understand.

08:27.884 --> 08:32.722
Soon, the Emperor arrives here,
and he expects to find order.

08:34.097 --> 08:35.474
Order!

08:37.934 --> 08:40.313
What is it you want of me, Prefect?

08:44.107 --> 08:46.694
Take control out there and finish things.

08:46.777 --> 08:48.779
This has gone on long enough.

08:51.949 --> 08:54.285
And do this Nazarene a small mercy.

08:56.120 --> 08:57.121
Break his legs.

08:59.207 --> 09:01.751
Clavius, meet your new aide.

09:03.419 --> 09:05.796
Lucius Tycho Ennius.

09:06.631 --> 09:08.382
His father's a friend.

09:10.801 --> 09:12.011
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTS)</font>

09:14.055 --> 09:15.806
It is an honor, Tribune.

09:19.810 --> 09:21.479
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAVIUS SIGHS)</font>

09:28.569 --> 09:30.112
<font color="#D900D9">(BELL CLANGS)</font>

09:30.655 --> 09:32.365
<font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER RUMBLING)</font>

09:33.783 --> 09:37.495
What sky is this?
Last hour, the sun was shining.

09:38.579 --> 09:39.956
- <font color="#D900D9">(LOUD RUMBLING)</font>
- <font color="#D900D9">(NEIGHING)</font>

09:40.039 --> 09:41.290
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> Whoa! Easy.

09:41.666 --> 09:43.146
- <font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING CONTINUES)</font>
- <font color="#D900D9">(MEN GASPING)</font>

09:46.170 --> 09:47.213
Easy.

09:52.843 --> 09:54.220
<font color="#D900D9">(PANICKED SHOUTS)</font>

09:54.303 --> 09:55.638
<font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING STOPS)</font>

09:56.681 --> 09:58.391
Poseidon's unhappy.

09:59.976 --> 10:01.352
Some god is.

10:06.065 --> 10:08.818
- <font color="#D900D9">(CLAMORING)</font>
- <font color="#808080">SOLDIER:</font> Move! Stand back!

10:16.409 --> 10:18.035
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN SCREAMING)</font>

10:18.119 --> 10:19.453
<font color="#808080">SOLDIER:</font> Get back!

10:21.706 --> 10:22.707
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN SOBS)</font>

10:22.790 --> 10:26.085
I hate it when they scream. I hate it.

10:26.627 --> 10:28.462
He could last for days, that one.

10:28.546 --> 10:30.047
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAMORING CONTINUES)</font>

10:31.716 --> 10:33.509
<font color="#808080">SOLDIER:</font> Get back now!

10:33.718 --> 10:35.136
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN SOBBING)</font>

10:35.678 --> 10:37.596
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> Centurion, how goes this?

10:38.931 --> 10:40.433
A strange day, Tribune.

10:40.516 --> 10:42.101
It was just a tremor.

10:42.601 --> 10:45.396
That and too much dark in the air.

10:46.314 --> 10:50.067
But this "king". Something's wrong.

10:50.568 --> 10:52.236
And the mob feel it.

10:52.653 --> 10:54.363
Smite a few. Show them the rod.

10:54.447 --> 10:55.865
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAMORING CONTINUES)</font>

10:55.948 --> 10:58.034
The Nazarene, is he dead yet?

10:59.243 --> 11:03.164
After only six hours, he can't be.

11:03.247 --> 11:04.582
Has he spoken?

11:06.250 --> 11:09.086
- Has he spoken?
- Just before the tremor.

11:11.464 --> 11:13.466
He said, "It's finished."

11:14.842 --> 11:16.260
See that it is.

11:20.306 --> 11:21.891
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFTLY)</font> Finally.

11:24.685 --> 11:26.187
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN SOBBING)</font>

11:29.607 --> 11:30.858
It won't be long now.

11:30.941 --> 11:32.109
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>

11:32.818 --> 11:34.904
- <font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>
- <font color="#D900D9">(CROWD SHOUTS)</font>

11:36.781 --> 11:37.782
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN SCREAMS)</font>

11:37.865 --> 11:39.283
<font color="#D900D9">(SHUDDERING)</font>

11:39.950 --> 11:41.243
- <font color="#D900D9">(THUMPS)</font>
- <font color="#D900D9">(CROWD SHOUTS)</font>

11:41.327 --> 11:43.120
<font color="#D900D9">(WAILING)</font>

11:43.621 --> 11:45.039
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN GRUNTING)</font>

11:46.624 --> 11:48.376
That's the Nazarene's mother.

11:49.001 --> 11:50.503
<font color="#D900D9">(MARY WAILING)</font>

11:52.088 --> 11:53.255
Hold!

11:56.717 --> 11:57.968
Use the pilum.

12:06.268 --> 12:07.853
<font color="#D900D9">(MARY CONTINUES SOBBING)</font>

12:08.312 --> 12:10.064
Get that woman to shut up.

12:12.108 --> 12:13.651
Keep her quiet!

12:14.485 --> 12:15.986
Aren't you the lucky one?

12:17.113 --> 12:18.656
<font color="#D900D9">(MARY YELLS)</font>

12:18.864 --> 12:20.032
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

12:20.116 --> 12:21.492
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD GASPING)</font>

12:22.660 --> 12:23.786
Ugh...

12:24.036 --> 12:26.622
<font color="#D900D9">(SHUDDERING)</font>
Surely this man was innocent.

12:26.747 --> 12:28.499
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAMORING CONTINUES)</font>

12:33.170 --> 12:37.550
Steel yourself, man.
Go on and tell the Prefect it's done.

12:41.137 --> 12:42.638
<font color="#D900D9">(MARY SOBBING)</font>

12:48.561 --> 12:50.062
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

12:55.025 --> 12:56.569
<font color="#D900D9">(HORSE HUFFING)</font>

12:57.194 --> 12:59.822
Disperse! It's over!

12:59.905 --> 13:01.449
Go on home!

13:01.532 --> 13:05.035
<font color="#808080">SOLDIER:</font>
Move! Leave now! Leave!

13:06.203 --> 13:08.497
You, go on! Go!

13:08.581 --> 13:11.834
- <font color="#D900D9">(GASPS AND EXHALES)</font>
- That's it, let go. That's it, let it go.

13:11.917 --> 13:13.169
Deep breath out.

13:15.546 --> 13:18.090
Deep breath. That's it.

13:19.800 --> 13:22.636
- That's it. Let it go.
- <font color="#D900D9">(INSECTS BUZZING)</font>

13:23.220 --> 13:25.639
- <font color="#D900D9">(BIRDS CAWING)</font>
- <font color="#D900D9">(BREATHING WEAKLY)</font>

13:27.266 --> 13:28.476
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

13:34.940 --> 13:36.233
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

13:37.818 --> 13:39.195
<font color="#D900D9">(STRAINING)</font>

13:47.828 --> 13:49.455
<font color="#D900D9">(FLIES BUZZING)</font>

13:50.080 --> 13:51.415
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

13:57.087 --> 13:59.048
<font color="#D900D9">(FLIES BUZZING)</font>

14:01.091 --> 14:02.426
<font color="#D900D9">(COUGHING)</font>

14:03.677 --> 14:05.221
Get the pliers.

14:15.898 --> 14:17.775
I never killed a king before.

14:18.567 --> 14:19.735
Wait!

14:20.945 --> 14:24.490
Tribune, I come from Pilate.
Please read this.

14:24.573 --> 14:26.492
- You're the Arimathean.
- I am.

14:33.707 --> 14:35.626
Your own family tomb?

14:36.669 --> 14:38.087
What's he to you?

14:39.505 --> 14:43.050
The Sabbath is almost here.
I have merely two hours.

14:43.676 --> 14:44.843
Please.

14:49.390 --> 14:50.474
He's yours.

14:51.684 --> 14:53.143
Nicodemus, hurry.

14:55.896 --> 14:57.690
- Mary. Shh.
- <font color="#D900D9">(SOBBING)</font>

15:12.371 --> 15:13.622
Leave him.

15:15.332 --> 15:16.500
Sir?

15:17.001 --> 15:19.670
Go and find your centurion.
These will bury him.

15:35.019 --> 15:37.021
<font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER RUMBLING)</font>

15:47.406 --> 15:48.907
Please, Tribune.

15:55.664 --> 15:57.875
Gently. Gently.

16:11.513 --> 16:13.932
<font color="#808080">PILATE:</font>
Come, Clavius, soak this day away.

16:14.558 --> 16:16.393
Fill his cup. Keep it filled.

16:17.770 --> 16:21.315
What do you desire?
A meal? A massage? A girl?

16:22.274 --> 16:23.317
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

16:23.400 --> 16:25.027
Just this.

16:25.110 --> 16:26.445
You're young.

16:27.112 --> 16:29.323
A night's rest, you'll do it all again.

16:30.658 --> 16:31.784
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

16:32.034 --> 16:35.788
Your service is valued, Tribune.
I rely on it.

16:36.789 --> 16:41.502
So ask pardon, if today I seemed vexed.

16:41.585 --> 16:43.003
No matter.

16:43.921 --> 16:45.756
Is the Nazarene entombed?

16:47.424 --> 16:51.095
I helped push the stone
against it myself. Huge stone.

16:51.178 --> 16:52.388
Many admirers.

16:52.471 --> 16:54.640
Let's hope that's buried with him.

16:55.224 --> 16:56.684
It's a strange case.

16:56.767 --> 17:00.437
I've never seen a death so wished for,
even by him.

17:00.521 --> 17:03.273
It's as if he wanted to be sacrificed.

17:03.607 --> 17:06.609
- They are fanatics. Yahweh deranges them.
- <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

17:06.694 --> 17:10.614
Yes. No other gods and all that.
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

17:11.073 --> 17:16.537
I myself pray only to Minerva,
for wisdom. You?

17:16.619 --> 17:18.288
Mars.

17:18.372 --> 17:19.790
Of course.

17:20.624 --> 17:24.545
Well, let's hope one of them hears us.
I could use the help.

17:26.463 --> 17:28.382
One does what one must.

17:28.464 --> 17:30.509
I don't wish the mantle you wear.

17:31.009 --> 17:33.679
Spare me. It's your path, too.

17:38.684 --> 17:40.769
Your ambition is noticed.

17:44.189 --> 17:45.899
Where do you hope it will lead?

17:46.859 --> 17:48.152
Rome.

17:49.486 --> 17:50.654
And?

17:51.071 --> 17:53.532
Position. Power.

17:53.615 --> 17:56.368
- Which brings?
- Wealth.

17:57.119 --> 18:01.206
A good family.
Someday, a place in the country.

18:01.290 --> 18:02.916
Where you'll find?

18:03.000 --> 18:04.710
<font color="#D900D9">(BREATHES DEEPLY)</font>

18:05.878 --> 18:07.838
An end to travail.

18:09.798 --> 18:11.717
A day without death.

18:13.343 --> 18:14.887
Peace.

18:15.929 --> 18:17.890
All that for peace?

18:19.349 --> 18:21.185
Is there no other way?

18:23.979 --> 18:25.230
Well,

18:25.939 --> 18:27.316
I'm to bed.

18:27.399 --> 18:29.943
Tomorrow promises further punishment.

18:34.948 --> 18:38.660
The Nazarene, did you find him different?

18:39.953 --> 18:41.538
I found him dead.

18:42.706 --> 18:44.041
So you did.

18:45.125 --> 18:48.003
- Peace, Tribune, and good night.
- Good night.

19:04.353 --> 19:07.064
A coin for the ferryman.

19:08.899 --> 19:12.069
Journey well, Gaius Aelius.

19:14.530 --> 19:16.073
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> Legion, forward.

19:38.637 --> 19:39.930
Legion 10.

19:40.013 --> 19:41.765
<font color="#808080">ALL:</font> Fretensis!

20:04.288 --> 20:06.498
Tribune, Pilate summons you.

20:13.881 --> 20:15.716
<i>Salve,</i> Prefect.

20:16.842 --> 20:18.844
<font color="#D900D9">(SNIFFS QUIETLY)</font>

20:19.094 --> 20:21.513
You smell of meat. A feast?

20:22.389 --> 20:23.724
A funeral.

20:24.349 --> 20:27.686
There's your solution. Burn him in public.

20:28.312 --> 20:30.230
God forbids cremation.

20:30.314 --> 20:34.026
He also forbids labor on the Sabbath,
and yet here you are.

20:35.110 --> 20:36.320
Tribune.

20:37.487 --> 20:40.782
- Burn who?
- The crucified Nazarene.

20:40.866 --> 20:43.076
- Why?
- He's business unfinished.

20:43.160 --> 20:46.246
The man's dead, Caiaphas.
His followers are in hiding.

20:46.330 --> 20:49.374
He's no longer a threat
to your monopoly on piety.

20:50.542 --> 20:53.003
But still a threat, Prefect.

20:53.837 --> 20:58.091
While alive, that deceiver said
he would rise again after three days.

20:59.051 --> 21:01.011
He foretold it.

21:01.094 --> 21:03.722
We request that the sepulcher be sealed,

21:03.805 --> 21:07.601
lest his disciples come in the night,
steal the body

21:07.684 --> 21:10.854
and say that he is risen from death.

21:12.522 --> 21:16.610
That would cause more unrest in this city
than all his blasphemies combined.

21:16.693 --> 21:18.987
You have your own guard.
Secure it yourself.

21:19.071 --> 21:20.614
My words exactly.

21:20.697 --> 21:24.409
<font color="#808080">CAIAPHAS:</font> To which I replied,
"We need a Roman seal."

21:24.493 --> 21:28.705
This must be seen
as the impartial will of the Prefect.

21:28.789 --> 21:30.332
And not yours.

21:31.166 --> 21:33.710
We seek only what Caesar seeks.

21:34.169 --> 21:37.297
Peace in Jerusalem, peace in Judaea.

21:37.673 --> 21:41.259
Which you will lose if this body vanishes.

21:44.304 --> 21:45.514
Hence my summoning.

21:46.640 --> 21:48.058
Just see to it.

21:48.225 --> 21:50.936
- <font color="#D900D9">(STONE RUMBLING)</font>
- <font color="#D900D9">(MEN GRUNTING)</font>

21:59.569 --> 22:01.238
Satisfy yourself.

22:15.919 --> 22:17.629
- Seal it.
- <font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> Seal.

22:21.967 --> 22:23.760
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

22:42.696 --> 22:44.114
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFTLY)</font> Huh. Hey.

22:46.283 --> 22:49.661
No one touches those seals
before sunset tomorrow. Understood?

22:51.580 --> 22:53.290
Then tell the priests.

22:57.794 --> 22:59.212
Where's your centurion?

22:59.296 --> 23:02.049
He's not himself, sir.
Not since yesterday.

23:02.549 --> 23:04.051
Is that what pains you?

23:04.134 --> 23:06.053
No, sir. No.

23:09.848 --> 23:13.018
It's just... We were to have the night off.

23:14.144 --> 23:15.896
I'll have rations sent.

23:17.814 --> 23:19.274
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

23:28.533 --> 23:30.786
You're Sanhedrin, too, are you not?

23:33.455 --> 23:34.539
Yes.

23:35.373 --> 23:38.376
Your brothers despise this man,
yet you mourn him.

23:39.669 --> 23:41.588
He was very special.

23:42.339 --> 23:44.049
Hmm. A king?

23:47.511 --> 23:49.262
You test me, Tribune.

23:50.347 --> 23:53.308
What was his name?
The Nazarene.

23:58.688 --> 24:00.398
He was called Yeshua.

24:06.530 --> 24:07.697
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Move.

24:36.893 --> 24:38.728
<font color="#D900D9">(DOORS CREAKING)</font>

24:42.274 --> 24:45.902
He forgot. You know he did.

24:45.986 --> 24:48.655
They'd have sent food by now
if he had told them.

24:48.738 --> 24:50.115
He's an officer.

24:50.198 --> 24:53.326
Yeah, if we'd forgot,
could you fathom the beating?

24:57.581 --> 24:59.916
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFTLY)</font>
I was saving it for supper, but...

25:04.629 --> 25:08.341
Oh, you prince! You absolute champion.

25:08.425 --> 25:09.926
Oh, yeah.

25:10.302 --> 25:12.345
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>
I thought the night was lost.

25:14.598 --> 25:18.393
<font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER RUMBLING IN THE DISTANCE)</font>

25:27.485 --> 25:29.446
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTER)</font>

25:40.040 --> 25:43.043
- Tribune, Pilate...
- Summons me.

25:47.005 --> 25:49.883
- He's gone.
- The Nazarene?

25:49.966 --> 25:53.178
Of course, the Nazarene.
His tomb is stone empty.

25:53.261 --> 25:56.640
- Who brought this news? The guards?
- Your guards are missing!

25:56.723 --> 25:59.809
Some simpleton reported it.
Who did you put on the detail?

25:59.893 --> 26:03.230
I want them found and lashed.
To death, preferably.

26:03.313 --> 26:04.564
Let me investigate.

26:04.648 --> 26:08.735
That would be helpful, before Caiaphas
and his pack of raving Jews show up here.

26:08.818 --> 26:10.153
Too late.

26:12.239 --> 26:13.490
Tribune.

26:15.784 --> 26:19.871
Shall we dispense with lies?
The guards have told me.

26:19.955 --> 26:21.206
They came to you?

26:21.289 --> 26:25.210
Seeking sanctuary.
They know the penalty for sleeping on duty.

26:25.335 --> 26:28.630
- <font color="#808080">PILATE:</font> What happened?
- Exactly as I had predicted.

26:28.713 --> 26:32.092
The heretic's disciples
came in the night and stole the body.

26:32.801 --> 26:35.387
Already, they are proclaiming him
risen from death.

26:35.470 --> 26:37.138
Will the people believe it?

26:37.639 --> 26:40.183
<font color="#808080">CAIAPHAS:</font>
The weak will. Others want to.

26:40.267 --> 26:42.769
So we must announce the theft.

26:42.852 --> 26:44.521
<font color="#808080">PILATE:</font> Will they believe you?

26:44.938 --> 26:48.817
They'll believe the guards,
if you don't kill them first.

26:48.900 --> 26:50.944
<font color="#808080">PILATE:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS HEAVILY)</font>
Endless.

26:51.027 --> 26:54.239
Proclaim it before this blossoms.

26:54.322 --> 26:56.032
It's not enough.

26:56.658 --> 27:00.495
Without a corpse to prove him dead,
we have a potential Messiah.

27:01.663 --> 27:05.500
I want no doubt.
Tiberius cannot arrive to unrest.

27:05.583 --> 27:07.877
We must find a body.

27:09.713 --> 27:13.675
- Will you help?
- Of course. But proclaim it.

27:15.552 --> 27:18.221
Was my confidence in you
misplaced, Tribune?

27:18.680 --> 27:21.474
Perhaps you'd prefer a post in hell.

27:22.517 --> 27:25.603
You will track down
each and every one of these disciples.

27:25.687 --> 27:29.899
But more importantly, you will find
the corpse of this cursed Yeshua

27:30.483 --> 27:32.027
before it rots.

27:33.278 --> 27:34.779
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAVIUS SIGHS)</font>

27:35.989 --> 27:37.615
<font color="#D900D9">(HORSE NEIGHING)</font>

27:50.503 --> 27:52.255
<font color="#D900D9">(BIRDS CHIRPING)</font>

28:01.306 --> 28:03.058
Bring the Arimathean.

28:03.141 --> 28:04.976
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> You, get the Arimathean.

28:12.984 --> 28:14.235
<font color="#D900D9">(HORSE WHINNIES)</font>

28:22.327 --> 28:23.995
As if they burst.

28:30.126 --> 28:31.795
<font color="#D900D9">(INSECT BUZZING)</font>

28:33.505 --> 28:35.131
<font color="#D900D9">(LIQUID TRICKLING)</font>

28:41.596 --> 28:43.640
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Tribune, see this.

28:58.905 --> 28:59.989
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

29:00.198 --> 29:02.283
Oh! <font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

29:02.992 --> 29:04.494
Oh, my!

29:05.286 --> 29:07.580
- Where has he gone?
- You tell me.

29:08.123 --> 29:10.291
The body, was it anointed?

29:12.085 --> 29:16.005
We had no time. We just wrapped him
with myrrh and aloe.

29:17.507 --> 29:21.302
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERS)</font> That's what you see,
sweat and herbs. Bring it.

29:24.848 --> 29:26.182
<font color="#D900D9">(INSECT BUZZING)</font>

29:26.516 --> 29:27.934
I want nothing touched here.

29:28.017 --> 29:30.687
Post a watch, have everything
leaving Jerusalem searched.

29:30.770 --> 29:33.523
Arrest anyone claiming the Nazarene lives,
and find out where they heard it.

29:33.606 --> 29:34.774
Yes, Tribune.

29:35.442 --> 29:37.819
And comb the city
for bodies dead in the last week.

29:37.902 --> 29:40.113
Examine each for marks of the crucified.

29:41.030 --> 29:42.198
Dig them up?

29:44.701 --> 29:48.079
Every one. And bring him to me presently.

29:49.372 --> 29:50.748
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTER)</font>

30:20.320 --> 30:21.488
Tribune.

30:21.571 --> 30:22.822
I said, "In private."

30:26.493 --> 30:28.077
Where's your fellow?

30:28.953 --> 30:30.622
He doesn't wish to speak.

30:31.206 --> 30:32.499
<font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font> Truly?

30:32.790 --> 30:35.543
Well, he had no trouble
avowing the Nazarene's theft.

30:36.085 --> 30:38.588
He's afraid, as am I.

30:39.172 --> 30:40.882
So you should be.

30:41.841 --> 30:46.012
You disgraced me.
And sleeping on post means death.

30:47.931 --> 30:49.933
But the Prefect has spared you.

30:50.725 --> 30:52.519
You both can return to barracks.

30:53.937 --> 30:55.355
Unpunished?

30:55.438 --> 30:58.274
If you bare yourself honestly
about what happened.

31:02.362 --> 31:06.950
We were attacked in the night while
sleeping by the Nazarene's rabid disciples.

31:08.076 --> 31:10.620
They stole his body
and bade us say he is risen.

31:11.287 --> 31:12.455
Rabid?

31:13.248 --> 31:14.666
How many attacked you?

31:15.291 --> 31:18.127
Eight. Ten. I'm not sure.

31:18.211 --> 31:20.630
- All armed?
- Yes.

31:21.047 --> 31:22.840
And you saw this while sleeping?

31:23.466 --> 31:25.969
No. No, I... We, um...

31:27.178 --> 31:29.889
We awoke as they were cutting the ropes.

31:29.973 --> 31:31.724
- Cutting them?
- Yes.

31:31.808 --> 31:32.892
Yes.

31:34.894 --> 31:36.854
And then they rolled away the stone,

31:37.647 --> 31:39.148
took his body and ran.

31:39.941 --> 31:41.359
While you watched?

31:41.943 --> 31:44.862
<font color="#D900D9">(STUTTERS)</font>
Yes, but we were held at spear point.

31:45.947 --> 31:47.156
Soldier,

31:48.324 --> 31:50.743
have you been told to say these things?

31:50.827 --> 31:51.828
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERING)</font>

31:55.665 --> 31:57.584
- Were you drinking that night?
- No.

31:57.667 --> 31:59.502
- No?
- No.

32:02.714 --> 32:04.382
What else is a lie?

32:29.657 --> 32:31.326
Open the doors!

32:33.953 --> 32:36.039
- Stolen?
- So they claim.

32:36.122 --> 32:37.790
Well, so what?

32:38.374 --> 32:40.793
They really fear he rose from death.

32:41.794 --> 32:44.589
Mmm-hmm. Perhaps the Messiah.

32:46.758 --> 32:48.343
Anyway, so I heard.

32:49.844 --> 32:51.512
Arrest him.

32:51.596 --> 32:53.264
- Turn him.
- <font color="#D900D9">(GROANS, COUGHS)</font>

32:53.556 --> 32:56.225
- <font color="#D900D9">(INSECTS BUZZING)</font>
- <font color="#D900D9">(MAN RETCHING)</font>

32:57.560 --> 32:58.895
How old is this one?

33:00.021 --> 33:01.147
<font color="#808080">GUARD:</font> At least a week.

33:01.230 --> 33:03.566
- These?
- The thieves he died with.

33:04.233 --> 33:05.860
- <font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> We're done.
- <font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

33:06.903 --> 33:09.364
In two days, he'll be unrecognizable.

33:12.158 --> 33:13.951
Wait till you see combat.

33:21.084 --> 33:23.044
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD SHOUTING)</font>

33:30.176 --> 33:31.594
<font color="#D900D9">(LUCIUS CLEARS THROAT)</font>

33:32.220 --> 33:33.429
No.

33:33.513 --> 33:36.140
The hand's missing,
but see the hole in the other?

33:36.224 --> 33:38.643
Not him. Legs are broken.

33:39.811 --> 33:44.107
That's why we need your eyes, Tribune.
This grave here is very hasty and shallow.

33:50.446 --> 33:51.447
<font color="#D900D9">(SNIFFS)</font>

33:54.450 --> 33:55.618
Well?

33:56.577 --> 34:00.081
Two score, we questioned.
Eleven, I think, you should examine.

34:00.164 --> 34:03.042
One, I suspect, could be a disciple.

34:04.669 --> 34:05.962
<font color="#D900D9">(GAGGING)</font>

34:06.754 --> 34:07.755
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTS)</font>

34:07.922 --> 34:10.925
- Forgive me, Tribune.
- Take some chicory.

34:11.217 --> 34:14.094
In time, the stomach numbs to these things.

34:14.554 --> 34:17.348
- Now bring them in, one by one.
- Sir.

34:20.184 --> 34:21.310
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

34:24.480 --> 34:25.815
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> <i>Who took the body?</i>

34:26.399 --> 34:28.067
I don't know.

34:28.275 --> 34:32.822
They say you are an honest man
and also a follower of Yeshua.

34:35.366 --> 34:38.703
Truth will not prove fatal today.

34:40.413 --> 34:43.373
I was moved by what he said
and what he taught.

34:45.083 --> 34:46.960
And felt he didn't deserve such a death.

34:47.043 --> 34:49.045
They ripped open your
tomb to steal a corpse

34:49.130 --> 34:52.257
to promote a lie
that threatens Rome and the Sanhedrin.

34:52.341 --> 34:54.969
It was not Yeshua's followers.

34:55.553 --> 34:56.971
Not the true ones.

34:57.847 --> 34:59.599
They are heartbroken.

35:02.518 --> 35:04.145
Some say he is risen

35:06.189 --> 35:08.316
to lead Israel against us.

35:09.942 --> 35:11.444
The Messiah.

35:13.362 --> 35:14.947
Do you believe that?

35:17.116 --> 35:18.659
If he had lived,

35:19.869 --> 35:22.663
I believe Yeshua
would embrace you as a brother.

35:25.583 --> 35:27.376
Even as you slew him.

35:28.377 --> 35:29.712
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

35:32.548 --> 35:33.716
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFTLY)</font> Leave us.

35:38.888 --> 35:42.225
I will try other means
before I am forced to break you.

35:47.438 --> 35:50.566
One thing has been
withheld from you, Tribune.

35:51.484 --> 35:52.902
I confess.

35:53.569 --> 35:56.781
You asked if he was a king.

36:03.621 --> 36:05.540
I return his crown.

36:10.169 --> 36:11.254
<font color="#808080">LUCIUS:</font> Sit.

36:21.639 --> 36:22.932
Why do you tremble?

36:24.016 --> 36:25.601
You're a Roman.

36:27.979 --> 36:31.274
You were heard shouting,
"Yeshua yet lives."

36:32.984 --> 36:35.611
Joyously, says the report.

36:36.237 --> 36:38.322
Why? You obviously didn't see him.

36:38.406 --> 36:40.533
<font color="#808080">MIRIAM:</font> I heard it on the street.

36:40.616 --> 36:43.619
- From passersby?
- No.

36:44.412 --> 36:47.039
- I heard him.
- Yeshua.

36:47.123 --> 36:48.791
Two days ago.

36:49.625 --> 36:52.253
I know voices. I hear them.

36:52.336 --> 36:53.629
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> I have no doubt.

36:54.380 --> 37:00.219
Were you a follower of the Nazarene, Miriam?
Or just a follower of a follower?

37:01.637 --> 37:03.055
He loved me.

37:04.181 --> 37:05.641
An old woman.

37:06.642 --> 37:08.561
He lifted me up.

37:09.687 --> 37:11.355
Lifted you?

37:12.523 --> 37:14.859
If you knew him, you'd understand.

37:15.484 --> 37:18.821
Stop spreading rumors
men are lifted from death.

37:21.407 --> 37:22.658
<font color="#D900D9">(GENTLY)</font> Come.

37:23.075 --> 37:24.160
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAVIUS SIGHS DEEPLY)</font>

37:26.662 --> 37:28.664
Don't you wish to know what he said?

37:28.748 --> 37:30.583
Of course.

37:30.666 --> 37:34.670
"You are seeds already cast."

37:36.339 --> 37:37.381
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

37:37.506 --> 37:40.134
- You're too late.
- <font color="#808080">LUCIUS:</font> Come.

37:52.438 --> 37:53.773
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

37:57.360 --> 37:59.612
Next one, Tribune. Next one, I believe.

38:23.886 --> 38:27.640
I pray not to thee today, divine Mars,
but to the god of the Hebrews, Yahweh.

38:27.723 --> 38:28.891
Hear me.

38:29.892 --> 38:33.688
Take back your favor in defense of these
people I seek, and relinquish them to me.

38:33.771 --> 38:36.941
If you do this with clear
and recognizable signs,

38:37.024 --> 38:40.528
I vow to erect temples for you
and initiate games in your honor.

38:51.580 --> 38:52.790
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAVIUS SIGHS)</font>

38:52.999 --> 38:54.542
Do you know what I seek?

38:55.751 --> 38:57.003
Yes.

38:57.920 --> 39:01.173
So, who told you
the crucified Nazarene is alive?

39:04.343 --> 39:07.304
A friend of a friend.

39:07.388 --> 39:10.141
A friend of Yeshua? Perhaps a disciple?

39:11.142 --> 39:14.270
Whatever you say, make it truth.

39:16.981 --> 39:19.567
This friend said he was told

39:21.027 --> 39:23.529
the sighting was told of by

39:24.071 --> 39:25.114
two women.

39:29.035 --> 39:33.789
They went to the tomb before dawn
that morning and found it empty.

39:37.418 --> 39:39.920
Then later met Yeshua on the road.

39:41.797 --> 39:43.007
Alive.

39:47.970 --> 39:49.305
Their names.

39:51.307 --> 39:52.767
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAVIUS SCOFFS)</font>

39:54.143 --> 39:57.980
One way or another,
we will have our answer.

40:01.484 --> 40:03.652
I know only one. <font color="#D900D9">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>

40:04.320 --> 40:06.072
A woman of the street.

40:07.281 --> 40:09.158
Mary Magdalene.

40:09.241 --> 40:12.745
Last time she was spotted was on
the morning the body was stolen. Early.

40:12.828 --> 40:15.414
Not seen since. That's all I have, Tribune.

40:15.498 --> 40:18.918
- Where does she work?
- Work? She's of the street.

40:20.002 --> 40:22.046
You're bringing no one to identify her?

40:22.755 --> 40:25.341
Wh... Who? Who would that be?

40:27.426 --> 40:28.427
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISTLES SHARPLY)</font>

40:29.970 --> 40:32.723
Who among you knows
the woman Mary Magdalene?

40:40.189 --> 40:44.235
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font>
They outflanked us, so we had to withdraw.

40:44.318 --> 40:46.028
A fighting retreat.

40:47.279 --> 40:50.366
Some dozen of our men were caught
and dragged up into the hills.

40:51.909 --> 40:56.539
Later that night, down in the valley,
we heard them screaming and looked up

40:57.206 --> 41:01.794
to see them staked out on the ridge tops
so we could watch.

41:04.213 --> 41:06.590
That is why you offer no quarter.

41:09.802 --> 41:11.220
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)</font>

41:12.847 --> 41:14.223
Is that her?

41:15.432 --> 41:16.809
No.

41:28.863 --> 41:30.197
That's her.

41:30.281 --> 41:31.699
- <font color="#D900D9">(BANGING)</font>
- Halt!

41:32.032 --> 41:33.742
<font color="#D900D9">(PATRONS SCREAMING)</font>

41:40.875 --> 41:41.876
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

41:48.841 --> 41:49.842
Aha.

41:51.051 --> 41:52.052
Mmm-hmm.

41:52.344 --> 41:54.263
<i>Shalom,</i> Mary.

41:55.890 --> 41:57.600
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> Why did you run from us?

41:58.601 --> 41:59.894
<font color="#808080">MARY MAGDALENE:</font> Instinct.

42:00.686 --> 42:02.396
I've seen you before.

42:04.565 --> 42:06.245
- <font color="#808080">MARY MAGDALENE:</font> My other life?
- <font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font>

42:07.151 --> 42:09.820
At Yeshua's death.
You were there beside his mother.

42:09.904 --> 42:12.573
Was she also the woman
with you at his tomb?

42:13.157 --> 42:15.451
<font color="#D900D9">(CRYING)</font>
If you knew what happened there,

42:16.577 --> 42:18.204
all cares would cease.

42:18.287 --> 42:19.872
Enlighten me, then.

42:19.955 --> 42:20.956
It's

42:21.832 --> 42:23.375
beyond us.

42:24.084 --> 42:26.921
Spare me the riddles and zealot babble.

42:28.631 --> 42:31.091
Where did you take Yeshua?

42:34.511 --> 42:36.096
He's right here.

42:36.180 --> 42:40.059
Is he a goblin? A sprite?
Alive again somehow?

42:41.977 --> 42:43.854
Open your heart and see.

42:43.938 --> 42:47.358
I see delusion to keep a crusade alive.

42:48.484 --> 42:52.321
I could have what I want pulled from you,
put you to death like that.

42:52.404 --> 42:53.739
It doesn't matter.

42:53.989 --> 42:55.157
Ah.

42:56.492 --> 42:58.535
- A martyr.
- No.

42:58.619 --> 43:01.163
Then give me the others,
and I'll grant you freedom.

43:02.164 --> 43:03.666
I'm already free.

43:05.584 --> 43:07.086
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

43:20.516 --> 43:22.351
Show me the Messiah.

43:23.936 --> 43:25.604
Alive or dead.

43:27.606 --> 43:29.608
And show me those who follow him.

43:32.361 --> 43:35.281
You look for something
you'll never find, Tribune.

43:39.285 --> 43:41.537
You look for the wrong thing.

43:50.379 --> 43:52.047
<font color="#D900D9">(BIRDS CAWING)</font>

43:55.592 --> 43:56.593
<font color="#D900D9">(LUCIUS CLEARS THROAT)</font>

43:59.430 --> 44:02.016
She's mad, refuses to talk sense.

44:02.725 --> 44:04.560
Perhaps a witch, sir.

44:05.102 --> 44:07.771
Should I have her stoned?
At least locked up?

44:09.064 --> 44:10.274
Just...

44:11.275 --> 44:12.484
Let her go.

44:13.986 --> 44:15.154
Sir?

44:16.697 --> 44:19.408
Release her. The woman's touched.

44:21.744 --> 44:25.956
Two days without sleep, Tribune.
You'll start seeing things.

44:35.674 --> 44:38.218
- When that turns, wake me.
- Sir.

44:39.928 --> 44:41.347
You, up.

44:44.141 --> 44:45.309
Move.

44:57.821 --> 44:59.615
<font color="#D900D9">(WAVES CRASHING)</font>

45:00.699 --> 45:02.076
<font color="#D900D9">(WIND HOWLING)</font>

45:15.297 --> 45:16.465
<font color="#808080">LUCIUS:</font> Tribune.

45:17.549 --> 45:20.761
Your sand has run out,
and Pilate summons you.

45:32.064 --> 45:33.899
You're digging up the dead?

45:33.982 --> 45:35.567
No stone unturned, Prefect.

45:35.651 --> 45:38.362
But a Hebrew cemetery?

45:39.488 --> 45:42.908
It seemed logical.
He's Jewish and deceased.

45:42.991 --> 45:43.992
<font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font>

45:44.827 --> 45:47.621
Do you not realize the wrath incurred?

45:48.414 --> 45:53.001
Another day or two, and wrath won't matter.
Nature will have taken its course.

45:54.378 --> 45:57.089
Caesar's spies will hear of all of this.

45:57.172 --> 45:59.341
An unfortunate dilemma.

46:04.138 --> 46:06.723
For both of us, Tribune.

46:06.807 --> 46:09.852
I want his body here by tonight.

46:16.442 --> 46:19.111
The disciples are key.
We find them, we find him.

46:22.614 --> 46:24.074
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> For your help.

46:25.117 --> 46:27.703
There's more if you assist us further.

46:29.872 --> 46:33.500
The Nazarene's disciples,
how many are there?

46:33.584 --> 46:37.171
Their names? Their plans?
Their weapon caches?

46:37.838 --> 46:39.923
Where do they gather? Who leads them now?

46:41.133 --> 46:43.135
Where are they hiding his corpse?

46:50.225 --> 46:51.727
Work quickly.

46:55.689 --> 46:57.191
There are 12.

47:04.573 --> 47:05.782
Well,

47:06.533 --> 47:08.243
11 now.

47:09.077 --> 47:10.913
Yeshua's inner circle.

47:11.830 --> 47:15.584
- All hiding. I know not where.
- Do you have names again?

47:20.881 --> 47:22.925
I'll give you one.

47:27.471 --> 47:28.472
<font color="#D900D9">(MEN GRUNTING)</font>

47:33.435 --> 47:34.978
Who's Bartholomew?

47:35.062 --> 47:36.271
I am he.

47:38.065 --> 47:39.233
Bring him.

47:41.735 --> 47:44.988
What do you hope to win
by spreading fantasy?

47:45.072 --> 47:48.367
By mine own eyes, Tribune,
I... I walked with him.

47:48.450 --> 47:52.538
He spoke to me.
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font> It's unbelievable, but it is so.

47:53.539 --> 47:54.873
Then conjure him up.

47:55.457 --> 47:56.500
Right now.

47:56.625 --> 47:57.626
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

47:57.709 --> 48:00.712
Or show me the body
he must have shed like a snake skin.

48:00.796 --> 48:03.298
God is not at my beck and call.

48:03.382 --> 48:04.508
God?

48:05.092 --> 48:09.304
Yahweh manifests himself
through a crazy, poor, dead Jew.

48:09.429 --> 48:10.514
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

48:10.639 --> 48:12.641
Well, so it appears.

48:13.392 --> 48:15.060
And what does this rebirth mean?

48:15.269 --> 48:16.436
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERS)</font>

48:17.354 --> 48:18.647
Eternal life.

48:19.231 --> 48:23.110
For everyone, everyone who believes.

48:23.193 --> 48:24.778
Marvelous recruiting tool.

48:26.530 --> 48:28.699
- Much better than salt.
- <font color="#D900D9">(SNICKERS)</font>

48:28.782 --> 48:29.992
How many are you?

48:30.075 --> 48:35.706
Well, we are few for now,
and our only weapon is love.

48:36.665 --> 48:41.336
But this, well, this changes everything.

48:42.671 --> 48:44.339
What are your intentions?

48:46.008 --> 48:50.596
Why do you fear him so?
This empire means nothing to him.

48:50.679 --> 48:55.851
"Render unto Caesar what is Caesar's."
That's what he taught us.

48:57.561 --> 48:59.521
What if I ordered your crucifixion?

48:59.771 --> 49:03.942
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERS)</font>
Well, I would happily submit. Strike.

49:08.322 --> 49:09.740
Ever watch a man crucified?

49:12.075 --> 49:13.285
No.

49:14.119 --> 49:15.329
No.

49:16.955 --> 49:20.917
I don't remember seeing you there,
probably because you ran.

49:22.878 --> 49:24.171
Didn't you?

49:25.380 --> 49:27.049
Shall I tell you what you missed?

49:30.302 --> 49:31.386
Feel it.

49:36.183 --> 49:39.645
Imagine having this
driven through your arms.

49:40.771 --> 49:44.358
And then the same driven through
your feet, your feet.

49:44.441 --> 49:45.859
Can you imagine it?

49:45.942 --> 49:50.739
It's what you hang from.
Nails, rubbing on bone.

49:52.199 --> 49:54.951
You have to decide what's worse.

49:55.744 --> 49:57.412
The agony here.

49:57.788 --> 49:59.081
<font color="#D900D9">(BARTHOLOMEW WINCES)</font>

49:59.247 --> 50:01.458
- Or here.
- <font color="#D900D9">(BARTHOLOMEW GROANS)</font>

50:01.708 --> 50:06.171
And choose which torture
your own weight will inflict constantly.

50:06.254 --> 50:08.799
And then you discover you can't breathe.

50:08.882 --> 50:11.885
And you realize
you will never breathe easily again.

50:11.968 --> 50:14.388
And that every breath
for the rest of your horrific life

50:14.471 --> 50:17.057
will be like sucking through wet cloth.

50:18.266 --> 50:20.143
Yeshua was lucky.
He only hung like that for hours.

50:20.227 --> 50:23.397
Most take days,
gasping for someone to kill them.

50:23.480 --> 50:25.691
And if he still felt anything at the end,

50:25.774 --> 50:29.861
he surely felt the spear thrust up under
his ribs to pierce his heart and lungs.

50:29.945 --> 50:33.240
I didn't watch closely, but they must have
had to break bones getting him down.

50:33.323 --> 50:35.784
- Sometimes, they bury them...
- Enough.

50:38.328 --> 50:40.372
- Enough.
- <font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

50:40.455 --> 50:42.708
Let's not speak any more of his body.

50:43.542 --> 50:47.879
It must be hideous to look upon by now.
But I ask you one last time.

50:48.672 --> 50:52.801
Where are the other disciples?
I will not ask again.

50:53.635 --> 50:56.179
Tell me, and you're free.

51:03.645 --> 51:05.230
Give your word.

51:06.982 --> 51:08.191
My word.

51:09.192 --> 51:10.485
Where are they?

51:28.003 --> 51:29.254
They're

51:32.466 --> 51:34.259
everywhere.

51:34.634 --> 51:37.137
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

51:53.153 --> 51:55.655
<font color="#D900D9">(HORSES WHINNYING)</font>

51:58.867 --> 52:00.827
<font color="#D900D9">(INSECTS BUZZING)</font>

52:06.541 --> 52:07.751
Are there any others?

52:10.253 --> 52:12.506
None that you could still recognize.

52:15.717 --> 52:16.843
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

52:17.052 --> 52:18.929
Are we finished, Tribune?

52:30.816 --> 52:32.067
It's him?

52:33.527 --> 52:37.781
See the nail holes here, here and here.

52:38.907 --> 52:40.408
The wound in the side.

52:40.909 --> 52:43.411
But the face. I can't tell.

52:44.996 --> 52:46.456
Nor can anyone else.

52:48.667 --> 52:49.793
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHING)</font>

52:52.295 --> 52:54.214
Let it be so, Prefect.

52:55.215 --> 52:58.426
At this point,
almost any corpse could be the Nazarene.

52:59.427 --> 53:01.763
I'll still find those who took him.
That's the threat.

53:02.347 --> 53:03.390
Threat

53:04.266 --> 53:06.101
is a creature with many heads.

53:07.435 --> 53:11.523
Right now, I need you elsewhere.
Trouble in Hebron.

53:13.275 --> 53:16.611
But something
yet needs unraveling with this.

53:16.695 --> 53:18.363
Just allow me until next week.

53:19.197 --> 53:22.784
Next week, I need you in Hebron.

53:27.205 --> 53:29.791
You are dangerously clever, Tribune.

53:30.834 --> 53:32.836
Can I turn my back on you?

53:33.920 --> 53:35.755
That's what I fear the most, Prefect.

53:35.839 --> 53:37.340
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

53:37.841 --> 53:39.426
From the same cloth.

53:40.969 --> 53:44.973
I remember when I was you, so sure, so...

53:45.765 --> 53:46.975
Uh...

53:47.684 --> 53:49.102
I forget.

53:49.185 --> 53:51.938
But in the end, what does
it all matter, really?

53:52.022 --> 53:53.189
Pardon?

53:55.567 --> 53:56.860
In a few years,

53:57.694 --> 53:58.987
that's us.

54:07.203 --> 54:08.455
<font color="#808080">TOWER <font color="#808080">GUARD:</font></font> Open!

54:09.080 --> 54:11.166
<font color="#D900D9">(GATE RATTLING)</font>

54:16.212 --> 54:17.631
What goes?

54:17.714 --> 54:21.718
Rumor has it we're heading to Hebron,
so I took the liberty, Tribune.

54:22.469 --> 54:24.346
Your tomb guards have been sighted.

54:25.513 --> 54:27.557
They finally fled the temple.

54:27.641 --> 54:29.768
- Where?
- It's unclear.

54:29.851 --> 54:31.978
But it is said
they have come into some money.

54:38.401 --> 54:40.362
I know you wish to triumph, sir.

54:41.655 --> 54:43.531
I know things will happen in time.

54:48.161 --> 54:50.163
Your ambition is noticed.

54:55.710 --> 54:57.712
- <font color="#808080">POLYBIUS:</font> Sing it!
- <font color="#D900D9">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

54:57.879 --> 54:59.464
<font color="#D900D9">(IN A DRUNK VOICE)</font>
That's the one.

54:59.547 --> 55:01.216
Sing the song.

55:01.758 --> 55:05.470
Sing... No, don't stop. Don't stop.

55:05.553 --> 55:08.848
Sing it again! Sing it again, please!

55:08.932 --> 55:11.726
Come on. That was good.
They're good, aren't they?

55:12.227 --> 55:14.688
Oh, yes, it's a nice song.

55:15.313 --> 55:17.399
It's a nice song. It's a nice...

55:22.570 --> 55:23.570
<font color="#D900D9">(SNIFFS)</font>

55:23.613 --> 55:27.158
Hmm. Pricey wine for a legionary.

55:29.536 --> 55:32.038
You've been hiding.
Where did you gain silver like this?

55:35.792 --> 55:36.918
Off a dead man.

55:37.002 --> 55:38.003
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

55:38.545 --> 55:39.671
Of course.

55:39.754 --> 55:40.922
So what?

55:42.674 --> 55:44.634
I was pardoned by the Prefect.

55:46.052 --> 55:47.262
Pardoned.

55:48.304 --> 55:50.265
Nothing can be done to me now.

55:51.349 --> 55:52.976
I said what they, uh...

55:53.768 --> 55:55.603
What was proclaimed.

56:03.028 --> 56:04.446
Say it again.

56:05.530 --> 56:07.115
Why?

56:07.198 --> 56:09.701
To see how your tale matches your mate's.

56:10.702 --> 56:12.203
<font color="#D900D9">(MUTTERS)</font>

56:14.414 --> 56:17.417
We were attacked in the night
while sleeping by the rabid disciples.

56:17.500 --> 56:19.169
The priests paid you to say this.

56:19.252 --> 56:23.214
They stole his body
and bade us say that he is risen.

56:24.591 --> 56:26.885
How did the stone
fall 10 paces from the tomb?

56:26.968 --> 56:29.888
It took seven men, myself included,
just to roll it closed.

56:29.971 --> 56:32.807
And the ropes weren't cut.
They were torn as if thread.

56:32.891 --> 56:35.393
The seals melted like butter.
Shall we go there?

56:35.477 --> 56:36.644
No!

56:37.896 --> 56:39.481
Why does it bother you so?

56:41.941 --> 56:43.318
No more lies.

56:44.319 --> 56:45.612
How did they take him?

56:46.279 --> 56:48.531
What happened to the Nazarene's body?

56:49.324 --> 56:50.825
You forgot us. <font color="#D900D9">(SOBS)</font>

56:53.203 --> 56:55.997
Forgot! We'd had no supper.

56:56.831 --> 57:01.044
That's why the wine made us slumber.
Yeah, yeah, yeah, we slept.

57:02.003 --> 57:03.004
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

57:03.129 --> 57:05.673
We'd been up two days
since the crucifixion.

57:05.757 --> 57:07.133
What could happen

57:08.009 --> 57:09.844
guarding the body of a dead man?

57:12.806 --> 57:15.767
So we closed our eyes
in turns for a bit until...

57:15.850 --> 57:17.102
Until what?

57:19.646 --> 57:22.065
Until we was wakened by this terrible...

57:24.150 --> 57:25.443
This terrible...

57:27.487 --> 57:28.863
This terrible flash.

57:29.697 --> 57:31.157
The night was gone.

57:31.950 --> 57:35.328
The air smelled burned,
and the ropes, they just...

57:35.411 --> 57:37.038
They just exploded.

57:37.122 --> 57:40.250
And the stone flew like a leaf.
And all of a sudden, the sun

57:42.252 --> 57:44.087
rose in the tomb.

57:44.796 --> 57:46.089
It was the sun.

57:47.215 --> 57:48.383
It was...

57:50.468 --> 57:52.554
It was everything.

57:52.637 --> 57:57.767
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERS)</font> And then a figure appeared
that I could not gaze upon

57:57.851 --> 58:00.478
because of the terrible light,

58:01.187 --> 58:02.438
<font color="#D900D9">(SNIFFLES)</font> and it wasn't a man.

58:03.231 --> 58:04.399
It wasn't.

58:05.066 --> 58:09.487
And there was this voice all around
I could not fathom.

58:09.571 --> 58:12.866
And then we went running.
We ran so far and long.

58:12.949 --> 58:15.410
So far, until we could...

58:15.577 --> 58:17.078
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS AND WHIMPERS)</font>

58:17.245 --> 58:19.247
Until we could think again.

58:21.416 --> 58:22.417
<font color="#D900D9">(SNIFFLES)</font>

58:22.500 --> 58:27.714
And then we went and told the priests
because that's what you bade us do.

58:32.135 --> 58:35.013
And Caiaphas paid you
for a different story.

58:35.805 --> 58:37.056
Tribune,

58:38.224 --> 58:41.102
I have seen much
in the service of the Emperor.

58:41.895 --> 58:43.271
Cannibals and...

58:43.980 --> 58:46.191
And the Blue Celts in Gaul and, uh...

58:47.108 --> 58:51.112
I've seen a man taken by a serpent at sea.

58:53.406 --> 58:55.742
But never I witnessed a moment so, uh...

58:57.410 --> 58:58.703
So...

59:05.835 --> 59:07.420
Explain it to me.

59:13.343 --> 59:14.594
You were drunk.

59:16.012 --> 59:17.722
You saw the dawn burst.

59:19.891 --> 59:21.809
The wine you drank was tainted.

59:23.728 --> 59:24.896
Truly?

59:26.397 --> 59:27.815
Do you suppose?

59:28.650 --> 59:31.694
Maybe it was, uh, opium or frankincense?

59:31.778 --> 59:35.156
Maybe the disciples
stole the Nazarene's body with magic,

59:35.240 --> 59:36.783
as the priests said or...

59:38.868 --> 59:40.662
Maybe our story is true.

59:44.749 --> 59:46.459
What else could it be?

59:48.670 --> 59:50.004
I don't know.

59:52.840 --> 59:54.300
So I drink.

59:56.552 --> 59:57.804
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)</font>

01:00:03.017 --> 01:00:04.560
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

01:00:51.232 --> 01:00:52.358
<font color="#808080">LUCIUS:</font> Sir.

01:00:52.817 --> 01:00:53.943
Tribune.

01:00:55.945 --> 01:00:57.322
We have them.

01:00:57.488 --> 01:00:59.824
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

01:01:07.790 --> 01:01:09.375
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> It's the Romans!

01:01:10.585 --> 01:01:12.253
Come. Come quickly.

01:01:28.394 --> 01:01:31.856
- That's the house. That's where I lost him.
- Lost him?

01:01:31.939 --> 01:01:33.733
- I believe that's where he went in.
- You believe?

01:01:33.816 --> 01:01:38.488
Yes, sir. When coming to tell you,
I passed other disciples hurrying this way.

01:01:38.571 --> 01:01:41.532
They favor the upper room.
You didn't pay for that.

01:01:41.616 --> 01:01:42.617
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

01:01:42.700 --> 01:01:43.701
<font color="#D900D9">(SHEEP BLEATING)</font>

01:01:51.626 --> 01:01:53.544
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> It's the Romans. Quickly!

01:01:53.628 --> 01:01:55.046
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE SHOUTING)</font>

01:01:58.716 --> 01:01:59.842
<font color="#808080">LUCIUS:</font> Tribune.

01:01:59.926 --> 01:02:01.928
You six, this side.
Check every house, every room.

01:02:02.011 --> 01:02:05.556
You five, the other side.
I want at least two alive, so spare some!

01:02:05.640 --> 01:02:08.059
Go, go! Move! Come on, move!

01:02:08.142 --> 01:02:09.811
I'll block the end and work my way back!

01:02:15.316 --> 01:02:16.359
No!

01:02:27.662 --> 01:02:28.663
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

01:02:38.965 --> 01:02:40.174
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR SQUEAKING)</font>

01:03:05.867 --> 01:03:06.868
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING SOFTLY)</font>

01:03:24.469 --> 01:03:28.055
<font color="#D900D9">(ECHOING)</font> Tribune, anything? Tribune?

01:03:29.974 --> 01:03:33.269
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFTLY)</font> Nothing.
Stand down. Return to camp.

01:03:35.229 --> 01:03:37.607
Sir? Tribune?

01:03:38.149 --> 01:03:39.442
Stand down.

01:03:40.943 --> 01:03:42.487
Look for me shortly.

01:03:43.613 --> 01:03:46.991
Tribune. Sir, we are close. I can feel it.

01:03:47.074 --> 01:03:48.576
I don't need you for this.

01:03:54.499 --> 01:03:55.875
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFTLY)</font> I don't need you.

01:03:59.712 --> 01:04:00.880
Sir.

01:04:06.427 --> 01:04:07.595
<font color="#808080">LUCIUS:</font> Stand down!

01:04:08.262 --> 01:04:10.765
Soldiers, stand down!

01:04:11.474 --> 01:04:12.600
March on!

01:04:20.900 --> 01:04:22.985
<font color="#D900D9">(BREATHING HEAVILY)</font>

01:04:44.173 --> 01:04:45.883
<font color="#808080">YESHUA:</font> Welcome, Clavius.

01:04:51.138 --> 01:04:52.848
Come join us, brother.

01:04:58.229 --> 01:04:59.981
There are no enemies here.

01:05:02.149 --> 01:05:03.234
Thomas.

01:05:04.402 --> 01:05:07.154
- Lord.
- Thomas, where have you been?

01:05:07.280 --> 01:05:08.880
- <font color="#D900D9">(THOMAS SOBS QUIETLY)</font>
- <font color="#D900D9">(YESHUA LAUGHS)</font>

01:05:10.324 --> 01:05:11.450
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

01:05:13.327 --> 01:05:14.996
<font color="#D900D9">(YESHUA SHUSHING)</font>

01:05:15.621 --> 01:05:16.831
<font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font> I'm sorry.

01:05:20.626 --> 01:05:23.296
<font color="#808080">YESHUA:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERS)</font>
Sorry? Why are you sorry?

01:05:23.379 --> 01:05:25.965
Because I left you.

01:05:26.799 --> 01:05:27.925
<font color="#D900D9">(YESHUA CHUCKLES)</font>

01:05:28.801 --> 01:05:30.845
I'm alive. See?

01:05:33.014 --> 01:05:34.557
<font color="#D900D9">(THOMAS CRYING QUIETLY)</font>

01:05:39.186 --> 01:05:41.188
<font color="#808080">YESHUA:</font> We have nothing to fear.

01:05:42.773 --> 01:05:44.358
We are free.

01:05:48.154 --> 01:05:49.155
<font color="#D900D9">(YESHUA SHUSHING)</font>

01:05:54.076 --> 01:05:56.579
- <font color="#808080">YESHUA:</font> Touch this.
- <font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font> Your wound.

01:06:00.041 --> 01:06:01.334
And this.

01:06:05.546 --> 01:06:06.881
<font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font> Does it hurt?

01:06:15.806 --> 01:06:17.516
<font color="#D900D9">(QUIETLY)</font> How can this be?

01:06:23.564 --> 01:06:25.066
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL GASPS)</font>

01:06:25.816 --> 01:06:26.901
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> Yeshua?

01:06:28.027 --> 01:06:29.236
Yeshua?

01:06:30.613 --> 01:06:31.906
- <font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>
- <font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font> Yeshua?

01:06:34.533 --> 01:06:35.576
Yeshua?

01:06:35.660 --> 01:06:36.744
Is he coming back?

01:06:36.827 --> 01:06:38.107
<font color="#808080">MARY MAGDALENE:</font>
Where did he go?

01:06:39.914 --> 01:06:41.248
How would I know?

01:06:42.249 --> 01:06:43.584
What now?

01:06:44.210 --> 01:06:45.419
Simon?

01:06:47.004 --> 01:06:51.425
He said, "Stay in Jerusalem"
till we receive...

01:06:51.676 --> 01:06:52.677
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:06:52.760 --> 01:06:54.387
...some spirit.

01:06:54.887 --> 01:06:56.847
Well, what did we just receive?

01:06:56.931 --> 01:06:58.015
I don't know.

01:06:58.099 --> 01:07:00.017
- Galilee.
- What?

01:07:00.101 --> 01:07:02.311
When he appeared on the road,

01:07:02.395 --> 01:07:06.774
Yeshua said, "Tell my brothers to go
to Galilee, and there they'll see me."

01:07:06.857 --> 01:07:07.983
I told you this.

01:07:08.651 --> 01:07:10.111
We have seen him.

01:07:10.611 --> 01:07:12.321
In Galilee, you'll see him once more.

01:07:16.575 --> 01:07:17.743
And avoid them.

01:07:19.453 --> 01:07:20.705
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

01:07:21.288 --> 01:07:22.373
Simon?

01:07:27.044 --> 01:07:28.045
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:07:28.129 --> 01:07:29.296
Then we go.

01:07:30.131 --> 01:07:31.966
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

01:07:33.217 --> 01:07:35.057
- <font color="#808080">PETER:</font> We go, brothers.
- <font color="#808080">MATTHEW:</font> Be well, Mary.

01:07:35.803 --> 01:07:37.555
- <font color="#808080">BARTHOLOMEW:</font> Goodbye, Mary.
- <font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Farewell, Mary.

01:07:37.638 --> 01:07:38.681
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> Glory.

01:07:38.764 --> 01:07:40.484
<font color="#808080">MARY MAGDALENE:</font>
Goodbye, brothers. Farewell.

01:07:53.279 --> 01:07:54.613
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTER)</font>

01:07:59.243 --> 01:08:00.683
- <font color="#808080">SOLDIER #1:</font> Up there!
- <font color="#808080">SOLDIER #2:</font> Move!

01:08:02.163 --> 01:08:04.248
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)</font>

01:08:13.257 --> 01:08:14.425
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN GRUNTS)</font>

01:08:30.608 --> 01:08:32.193
Is it a ransom?

01:08:36.279 --> 01:08:37.698
"Do not seek me.

01:08:38.407 --> 01:08:40.408
"Do not follow or wonder.

01:08:41.493 --> 01:08:43.953
"Persecute no one on my behalf.

01:08:44.037 --> 01:08:48.542
"I have seen two things
which cannot reconcile.

01:08:49.710 --> 01:08:51.670
"A man dead without question

01:08:52.337 --> 01:08:55.716
"and that same man alive again.

01:08:56.716 --> 01:09:00.763
"I pursue him, the Nazarene,
to ferret the truth.

01:09:02.640 --> 01:09:05.392
"Clavius Aquila Valerius Niger."

01:09:07.728 --> 01:09:09.563
It's his seal, sir.

01:09:12.733 --> 01:09:16.569
- Must be a plague.
- My right hand turned against me.

01:09:18.072 --> 01:09:21.075
How could he follow that Hebrew?

01:09:22.158 --> 01:09:23.493
Perhaps

01:09:25.246 --> 01:09:26.622
it's true.

01:09:26.705 --> 01:09:28.122
Well, if it is,

01:09:29.291 --> 01:09:30.876
I'll kill him again.

01:09:31.710 --> 01:09:33.379
<font color="#D900D9">(WIND WHOOSHING)</font>

01:10:08.080 --> 01:10:09.206
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:10:21.719 --> 01:10:23.637
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> Brothers, we go.

01:10:37.318 --> 01:10:39.278
Alive, if you can.

01:10:39.987 --> 01:10:42.823
Although dead would be less embarrassing.

01:10:44.950 --> 01:10:46.744
I'll be in Caesarea.

01:10:48.162 --> 01:10:49.330
<font color="#808080">LUCIUS:</font> Sir.

01:10:51.665 --> 01:10:54.627
Moving out! North to Galilee.

01:11:00.966 --> 01:11:03.594
Ten days till the Emperor arrives.

01:11:05.262 --> 01:11:06.513
Ten days.

01:11:07.014 --> 01:11:08.349
Forward.

01:11:24.823 --> 01:11:26.367
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)</font>

01:11:30.037 --> 01:11:31.080
<font color="#D900D9">(BARTHOLOMEW LAUGHS)</font>

01:11:31.163 --> 01:11:32.539
Do you need some help, Thomas?

01:11:35.876 --> 01:11:37.196
- <font color="#D900D9">(BLADE SLICES)</font>
- <font color="#D900D9">(PETER SCREAMS)</font>

01:11:38.045 --> 01:11:39.129
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

01:11:42.007 --> 01:11:45.469
I brought water!

01:11:46.595 --> 01:11:47.846
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS IN PAIN)</font>

01:11:47.930 --> 01:11:49.348
<font color="#D900D9">(CONTINUES GROANING)</font>

01:11:55.062 --> 01:11:56.480
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>

01:12:05.197 --> 01:12:06.365
Water!

01:12:07.825 --> 01:12:09.576
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

01:12:12.579 --> 01:12:14.707
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)</font>

01:12:15.958 --> 01:12:17.251
<font color="#D900D9">(PETER GROANS)</font>

01:12:23.799 --> 01:12:26.468
That's a scar. I hope you know that.

01:12:29.722 --> 01:12:31.223
- What's wrong?
- What's wrong?

01:12:31.306 --> 01:12:34.435
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> <i>Yahweh, hallowed is your name.</i>

01:12:35.060 --> 01:12:37.730
Give us, today, this daily bread,

01:12:37.813 --> 01:12:42.943
and forgive us our debts,
as we have also forgiven our debtors.

01:12:43.777 --> 01:12:45.571
Lead us not into temptation,

01:12:54.955 --> 01:12:56.123
but

01:12:56.874 --> 01:12:58.292
away

01:12:59.793 --> 01:13:01.378
from evil.

01:13:04.381 --> 01:13:05.883
- Amen.
- Amen.

01:13:05.966 --> 01:13:07.509
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

01:13:09.053 --> 01:13:10.512
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAPPING HANDS)</font>

01:13:18.604 --> 01:13:20.147
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> But the son of Yahweh?

01:13:21.398 --> 01:13:22.900
And you believe it?

01:13:24.568 --> 01:13:26.153
And you believe it?

01:13:27.321 --> 01:13:29.948
After this, yes.

01:13:30.949 --> 01:13:33.577
He rises from death, eats, sleeps
and then disappears.

01:13:33.660 --> 01:13:34.787
<font color="#D900D9">(PETER SIGHS)</font>

01:13:36.663 --> 01:13:38.082
He has a body,

01:13:38.707 --> 01:13:41.335
the same vessel Yahweh gives all men.

01:13:41.418 --> 01:13:43.378
It is how he has reached out to us.

01:13:44.171 --> 01:13:45.297
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS HEAVILY)</font>

01:13:45.380 --> 01:13:46.507
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

01:13:47.257 --> 01:13:48.967
I haven't every answer.

01:13:50.511 --> 01:13:52.387
We're astounded, too.

01:13:55.182 --> 01:13:58.143
Why not just show himself to all,
then, hmm?

01:13:59.812 --> 01:14:02.064
Or can he be slain once more?

01:14:02.523 --> 01:14:04.274
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font> I don't know.

01:14:04.942 --> 01:14:07.569
I don't know, I don't know, I don't know.

01:14:08.445 --> 01:14:10.531
I wish I did, but I don't.

01:14:11.115 --> 01:14:12.533
The answers wait in Galilee?

01:14:13.492 --> 01:14:17.329
We are followers. We follow to find out.

01:14:27.047 --> 01:14:28.715
I think he is preparing us.

01:14:29.258 --> 01:14:30.676
For what?

01:14:31.135 --> 01:14:32.302
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:14:32.511 --> 01:14:33.512
<font color="#D900D9">(HORSES NEIGH)</font>

01:14:35.430 --> 01:14:36.640
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN SHOUTS IN THE DISTANCE)</font>

01:14:48.944 --> 01:14:50.320
- Down.
- Oh...

01:14:54.491 --> 01:14:56.577
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> Pilate will not let this rest.

01:14:57.077 --> 01:14:58.787
<font color="#D900D9">(CAMEL BELLOWS)</font>

01:14:59.037 --> 01:15:01.081
I bring danger to you all.

01:15:04.626 --> 01:15:06.253
They have a tracker.

01:15:10.841 --> 01:15:12.426
They can't know we're up here.

01:15:14.052 --> 01:15:15.053
<font color="#D900D9">(CAMEL GROANS)</font>

01:15:15.262 --> 01:15:17.014
They already do.

01:15:18.015 --> 01:15:19.683
<font color="#808080">TRACKER:</font> I found the enemy.

01:15:19.766 --> 01:15:21.768
And they're out for blood.

01:15:22.227 --> 01:15:24.104
<font color="#D900D9">(HORSES NEIGHING)</font>

01:15:27.983 --> 01:15:29.693
It doesn't scare us.

01:15:30.444 --> 01:15:32.112
Not anymore.

01:15:32.404 --> 01:15:33.780
<font color="#D900D9">(DISTANT CLAMORING)</font>

01:15:34.114 --> 01:15:37.075
Then fear the death
of what you're entrusted with.

01:15:39.161 --> 01:15:41.038
<font color="#D900D9">(CAMEL BELLOWS)</font>

01:15:41.288 --> 01:15:42.372
<font color="#D900D9">(HORSES NEIGHING)</font>

01:15:43.874 --> 01:15:45.626
<font color="#D900D9">(SOLDIER GRUNTING)</font>

01:15:55.302 --> 01:15:56.470
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERS)</font> Move back.

01:15:57.137 --> 01:15:58.472
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

01:16:06.146 --> 01:16:07.147
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> Down.

01:16:12.277 --> 01:16:13.987
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

01:16:18.951 --> 01:16:20.202
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> Put your head down.

01:16:20.285 --> 01:16:21.286
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

01:16:22.913 --> 01:16:24.831
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERS)</font>
Move, move. Move, move.

01:16:30.837 --> 01:16:32.130
<font color="#808080">TRACKER:</font> This way.

01:17:03.912 --> 01:17:05.747
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> Low. Come. Keep low.

01:17:06.873 --> 01:17:08.125
Stay down.

01:17:12.963 --> 01:17:13.964
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAVIUS GASPS)</font>

01:17:18.593 --> 01:17:21.555
- S...
- Beneficiarii, please.

01:17:21.847 --> 01:17:23.348
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAVIUS PANTING)</font>

01:17:23.890 --> 01:17:25.684
No quarter, Tribune.

01:17:26.560 --> 01:17:28.061
That's what you taught.

01:17:28.520 --> 01:17:30.063
A bad lesson.

01:17:30.188 --> 01:17:31.523
<font color="#D900D9">(SOLDIERS SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

01:17:31.606 --> 01:17:32.899
I give you the teacher.

01:17:36.069 --> 01:17:37.738
But let them pass.

01:17:37.821 --> 01:17:38.864
<font color="#808080">LUCIUS:</font> Mmm-mmm-mmm.

01:17:45.579 --> 01:17:46.997
The Nazarene?

01:17:47.998 --> 01:17:49.416
Vanished.

01:17:52.127 --> 01:17:53.253
<font color="#D900D9">(HISSES)</font>

01:17:55.088 --> 01:17:56.568
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERS)</font>
There are no enemies here.

01:17:56.673 --> 01:17:57.716
<font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font>

01:17:58.759 --> 01:17:59.968
<font color="#808080">SOLDIER:</font> Over here!

01:18:02.929 --> 01:18:06.266
You hold the world
in your hands, Beneficiarii.

01:18:07.225 --> 01:18:08.643
Know that.

01:18:10.479 --> 01:18:11.688
I believe

01:18:12.773 --> 01:18:14.691
it resides in these men.

01:18:25.035 --> 01:18:26.036
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

01:18:28.914 --> 01:18:30.457
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

01:18:32.751 --> 01:18:34.586
No one dies today.

01:18:38.340 --> 01:18:39.466
No one.

01:18:49.267 --> 01:18:50.477
Walk on.

01:18:52.312 --> 01:18:53.730
Say nothing.

01:18:55.565 --> 01:18:56.942
Remember this.

01:19:39.234 --> 01:19:40.861
<font color="#D900D9">(INAUDIBLE)</font>

01:19:54.124 --> 01:19:55.625
<font color="#D900D9">(SEABIRD SQUAWKING)</font>

01:19:57.878 --> 01:19:59.629
<font color="#808080">CLAVIUS:</font> Why do you think here?

01:19:59.713 --> 01:20:04.259
It was here that he called us to follow him.
Sometimes, he's hard to recognize.

01:20:04.718 --> 01:20:06.928
<font color="#808080">ANDREW:</font> Simon! Simon!

01:20:08.388 --> 01:20:10.640
Simon, they want to eat.

01:20:21.109 --> 01:20:22.736
Then let's fish.

01:20:23.653 --> 01:20:25.864
Let's fish! Come!

01:20:25.947 --> 01:20:27.824
<font color="#808080">ANDREW:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>
Come! Come on!

01:20:28.408 --> 01:20:29.659
He'll find us!

01:20:29.868 --> 01:20:31.411
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

01:20:32.913 --> 01:20:34.498
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL YELLING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

01:20:34.581 --> 01:20:35.707
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> Come on.

01:20:43.840 --> 01:20:45.592
<font color="#D900D9">(SEABIRD SQUAWKING)</font>

01:21:09.783 --> 01:21:12.786
We are here!

01:21:15.288 --> 01:21:16.414
Brothers,

01:21:18.416 --> 01:21:20.293
let's fish!

01:21:20.794 --> 01:21:21.795
<font color="#D900D9">(PETER GRUNTS)</font>

01:21:24.005 --> 01:21:27.634
Pull. Pull. That's it.

01:21:55.495 --> 01:21:56.496
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS EXHAUSTIVELY)</font>

01:22:00.542 --> 01:22:02.043
Cast again?

01:22:02.502 --> 01:22:04.671
<font color="#D900D9">(BOAT CREAKING)</font>

01:22:08.049 --> 01:22:09.467
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> Twice more.

01:22:10.135 --> 01:22:12.178
Then sleep till the sun wakes you.

01:22:13.513 --> 01:22:14.806
<font color="#D900D9">(SPLASHES)</font>

01:22:15.890 --> 01:22:17.100
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

01:22:46.212 --> 01:22:47.547
<font color="#808080">YESHUA:</font> Any luck?

01:22:50.717 --> 01:22:52.677
Try the right side again.

01:22:53.553 --> 01:22:54.888
<font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font>

01:23:02.312 --> 01:23:03.480
No.

01:23:08.610 --> 01:23:09.611
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> What...

01:23:13.657 --> 01:23:15.992
Brothers. Andrew. Move.

01:23:16.076 --> 01:23:17.744
- <font color="#808080">ANDREW:</font> What's happening?
- Prepare the net. John!

01:23:17.827 --> 01:23:19.287
- <font color="#808080">ANDREW:</font> Wake up.
- Philip. Brother.

01:23:19.371 --> 01:23:21.498
Spread. Prepare the nets.

01:23:21.873 --> 01:23:23.500
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

01:23:29.547 --> 01:23:30.757
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> Cast.

01:23:36.429 --> 01:23:37.764
<font color="#D900D9">(SHOUTING)</font>

01:23:41.351 --> 01:23:43.144
- What happened?
- Heave.

01:23:43.228 --> 01:23:46.606
- <font color="#808080">APOSTLE:</font> We're too shallow!
- We just did! We're stuck!

01:23:46.690 --> 01:23:50.443
- Heave it. Hoist the net, Andrew.
- It's caught on something.

01:23:50.527 --> 01:23:52.612
- <font color="#808080">PETER:</font> It's fish.
- We're stuck on the bottom.

01:23:52.696 --> 01:23:54.406
- We're not moving!
- It's fish.

01:23:56.533 --> 01:23:57.826
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> It's fish.

01:23:59.619 --> 01:24:00.787
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

01:24:01.579 --> 01:24:02.956
- It's fish!
- <font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

01:24:05.792 --> 01:24:07.127
Fish!

01:24:07.210 --> 01:24:08.378
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHTER CONTINUES)</font>

01:24:08.461 --> 01:24:10.213
How did you know?

01:24:11.965 --> 01:24:13.883
Faith! <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

01:24:14.426 --> 01:24:16.469
Yeshua!

01:24:16.553 --> 01:24:19.973
- <font color="#808080">APOSTLES:</font> It's him! It's him!
- Yeshua!

01:24:23.727 --> 01:24:25.270
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> Yeshua!

01:24:26.187 --> 01:24:27.397
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHTER CONTINUES)</font>

01:24:27.564 --> 01:24:28.982
Brothers.

01:24:30.316 --> 01:24:32.819
<font color="#808080">JOHN:</font> It's him! It's him.

01:24:50.837 --> 01:24:52.839
- <font color="#808080">PETER:</font> Pass it.
- <font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font> Thank you, Peter.

01:24:57.677 --> 01:24:59.345
- <font color="#808080">PETER:</font> Water?
- <font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font> No, thank you.

01:25:00.054 --> 01:25:03.016
Brother? Brother, water.

01:25:15.195 --> 01:25:17.030
<font color="#D900D9">(INAUDIBLE)</font>

01:25:20.825 --> 01:25:22.827
Did you know he would rise?

01:25:24.579 --> 01:25:27.081
He said he would,

01:25:27.832 --> 01:25:30.126
but, truth be told, we doubted it.

01:25:32.462 --> 01:25:35.006
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS SOFTLY)</font>

01:25:35.298 --> 01:25:37.258
Then what made you follow him?

01:25:38.301 --> 01:25:40.970
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> Leper! Go!
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

01:25:41.262 --> 01:25:42.430
Get out of here!

01:25:43.014 --> 01:25:44.182
Go!

01:25:46.392 --> 01:25:48.561
<font color="#808080">MEN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font> Leper! Leper!

01:25:48.645 --> 01:25:49.646
- Leper!
- Out!

01:25:49.729 --> 01:25:52.565
- Get out!
- Out! Out!

01:25:53.358 --> 01:25:55.819
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> Get out of here! Leper!
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

01:25:55.902 --> 01:25:57.403
Leper!

01:25:57.821 --> 01:25:59.030
Hmm.

01:25:59.113 --> 01:26:00.198
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE GRUNTING)</font>

01:26:11.543 --> 01:26:12.752
<font color="#D900D9">(WOMAN SPITS)</font>

01:26:17.507 --> 01:26:18.716
He's going to do it.

01:26:19.259 --> 01:26:20.593
Do what?

01:26:21.427 --> 01:26:22.947
<font color="#808080">THADDEUS:</font>
He's going to heal that man.

01:26:24.264 --> 01:26:25.265
<font color="#D900D9">(LEPER GROANS)</font>

01:26:25.348 --> 01:26:26.641
How?

01:26:27.267 --> 01:26:29.269
Watch. Just watch.

01:26:30.728 --> 01:26:32.689
No one touches me.

01:26:32.772 --> 01:26:34.065
A miracle.

01:26:34.691 --> 01:26:36.317
We saw them many times, Roman.

01:26:41.114 --> 01:26:43.491
<font color="#D900D9">(LEPER CRYING SOFTLY)</font>

01:26:45.827 --> 01:26:47.120
<font color="#808080">YESHUA:</font> Ah.

01:26:48.288 --> 01:26:49.706
<font color="#D900D9">(LEPER CONTINUES CRYING)</font>

01:26:50.540 --> 01:26:51.791
Mmm.

01:26:55.837 --> 01:26:57.517
- <font color="#808080">YESHUA:</font> Do you have faith?
- <font color="#D900D9">(LEPER SOBS)</font>

01:26:58.423 --> 01:26:59.799
Come, stand.

01:27:09.601 --> 01:27:10.768
Ah.

01:27:38.087 --> 01:27:39.380
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> Brothers.

01:27:45.136 --> 01:27:46.512
That's why.

01:27:55.772 --> 01:27:57.023
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES SLOWLY)</font>

01:27:57.941 --> 01:27:59.984
<font color="#D900D9">(BIRDS CHIRPING)</font>

01:28:17.043 --> 01:28:18.711
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> What do you search for?

01:28:20.421 --> 01:28:23.383
Trouble. It will come.

01:28:24.801 --> 01:28:27.387
This threatens them.

01:28:27.971 --> 01:28:30.264
Pilate, Caiaphas and Rome.

01:28:31.474 --> 01:28:33.309
Then there's trouble this way as well.

01:28:34.102 --> 01:28:35.645
Have faith, Tribune.

01:28:49.200 --> 01:28:52.245
<font color="#D900D9">(CHIRPING LOUDLY)</font>

01:28:56.249 --> 01:28:59.127
Peter, let's walk a little farther.

01:29:00.628 --> 01:29:02.130
Why?

01:29:02.213 --> 01:29:03.756
To be closer.

01:29:04.716 --> 01:29:06.551
Simon, do you love me?

01:29:07.593 --> 01:29:10.221
Yes. You know that I do.

01:29:12.015 --> 01:29:14.517
- <font color="#808080">YESHUA:</font> Do you love me?
- <font color="#808080">PETER:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font> Yes.

01:29:15.393 --> 01:29:18.563
- Simon, do you love me?
- With all my heart.

01:29:19.105 --> 01:29:21.190
Then you must feed my lambs.

01:29:25.361 --> 01:29:28.740
<font color="#D900D9">(CHIRPING AND WHOOSHING)</font>

01:29:55.892 --> 01:29:58.061
<font color="#D900D9">(ANIMAL HOWLING IN THE DISTANCE)</font>

01:30:09.238 --> 01:30:10.531
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS SOFTLY)</font>

01:30:51.614 --> 01:30:53.074
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES SLOWLY)</font>

01:30:59.455 --> 01:31:01.582
I don't even know what to ask.

01:31:05.461 --> 01:31:07.338
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFTLY)</font> Speak your heart.

01:31:08.714 --> 01:31:12.176
I cannot reconcile all this

01:31:14.720 --> 01:31:16.639
with the world I know.

01:31:18.141 --> 01:31:21.227
With your own eyes you've seen,
yet still you doubt.

01:31:22.603 --> 01:31:26.232
Imagine the doubt of those
who have never seen. That's what they face.

01:31:29.735 --> 01:31:31.571
What frightens you?

01:31:35.825 --> 01:31:37.410
Being wrong.

01:31:38.744 --> 01:31:40.913
Wagering eternity on it.

01:31:42.707 --> 01:31:44.125
Well, then,

01:31:45.835 --> 01:31:47.295
know Him.

01:31:55.761 --> 01:31:57.263
When you died,

01:32:02.602 --> 01:32:04.187
I was present.

01:32:08.065 --> 01:32:09.317
<font color="#D900D9">(VOICE BREAKING)</font>

01:32:09.775 --> 01:32:10.985
I helped.

01:32:11.736 --> 01:32:13.112
I know.

01:32:21.454 --> 01:32:24.248
What is it you seek, Clavius?

01:32:26.542 --> 01:32:29.420
Certainty? Peace?

01:32:31.255 --> 01:32:33.174
A day without death?

01:32:44.143 --> 01:32:45.645
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS SOFTLY)</font>

01:33:19.262 --> 01:33:21.097
<font color="#808080">PHILLIP:</font> Wake up, brothers!

01:33:21.180 --> 01:33:23.599
- Brothers, wake up. James, he's gone!
- Brothers, wake up, wake up.

01:33:23.683 --> 01:33:24.767
<font color="#808080">APOSTLE #1:</font> He's gone.
<font color="#808080">APOSTLE #2:</font> What?

01:33:24.850 --> 01:33:26.269
- <font color="#808080">PHILLIP:</font> Yeshua is gone.
- John, wake up!

01:33:26.352 --> 01:33:27.937
- Brothers!
- Yeshua!

01:33:28.020 --> 01:33:30.648
- <font color="#808080">APOSTLE #3:</font> Where is he?
- <font color="#808080">APOSTLE #4:</font> Come on, brothers.

01:33:30.731 --> 01:33:33.317
- Where's he gone?
- Yeshua!

01:33:33.401 --> 01:33:35.736
- Yeshua!
- Where is he?

01:33:35.820 --> 01:33:37.989
- Yeshua!
- Yeshua!

01:33:38.072 --> 01:33:40.533
- Yeshua!
- Brother!

01:33:41.575 --> 01:33:44.412
<font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING)</font>

01:33:53.546 --> 01:33:54.672
<font color="#808080">PETER:</font> Brothers.

01:34:04.098 --> 01:34:06.559
<font color="#D900D9">(ECHOING)</font> I go to prepare a place for you.

01:34:08.853 --> 01:34:10.062
Go

01:34:10.771 --> 01:34:13.607
into all the world and preach the gospel

01:34:14.317 --> 01:34:16.027
to all nations.

01:34:17.069 --> 01:34:19.822
You will be my witnesses in Jerusalem

01:34:20.406 --> 01:34:24.285
and all Judaea and Samaria
and to the ends of the earth.

01:34:29.957 --> 01:34:32.335
And know that I will be with you.

01:34:33.336 --> 01:34:34.670
Always.

01:34:38.132 --> 01:34:39.884
<font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING CONTINUES)</font>

01:34:42.928 --> 01:34:44.263
<font color="#D900D9">(WIND HOWLING)</font>

01:34:53.981 --> 01:34:55.024
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>

01:35:02.406 --> 01:35:03.449
Lord?

01:35:12.917 --> 01:35:14.835
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL SOBBING)</font>

01:35:17.630 --> 01:35:18.631
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:35:30.267 --> 01:35:32.895
<font color="#808080">JOHN:</font> It's not just about life eternal.

01:35:32.978 --> 01:35:37.274
It's how life is lived,
by the sword or by love.

01:35:37.691 --> 01:35:40.736
And it changes you here.

01:35:40.820 --> 01:35:41.987
It's time.

01:35:42.071 --> 01:35:43.322
Bye, brothers.

01:35:43.906 --> 01:35:46.325
- That's actually rather good.
- Mmm, it's beautiful.

01:35:46.409 --> 01:35:48.244
I may use that again.

01:35:48.327 --> 01:35:49.453
<font color="#808080">ALL:</font> Amen.

01:35:49.537 --> 01:35:50.704
Amen.

01:35:50.788 --> 01:35:52.540
- Bye, brothers.
- Peace be with you, brothers.

01:35:52.623 --> 01:35:53.666
Farewell.

01:35:53.749 --> 01:35:56.335
- Till the next time we meet in his presence.
- Goodbye, brother.

01:35:59.839 --> 01:36:01.882
- Bless you, Peter.
- <font color="#808080">MATTHEW:</font> Farewell.

01:36:05.594 --> 01:36:07.054
- <font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font> Take care, brothers.
- Take care.

01:36:07.138 --> 01:36:08.639
Farewell, brothers.

01:36:15.062 --> 01:36:16.355
Join us, Tribune.

01:36:19.567 --> 01:36:21.444
Jerusalem only bodes trouble.

01:36:21.777 --> 01:36:27.616
Ah, trouble and this spirit he promised.
We are called to receive it there, Roman.

01:36:27.700 --> 01:36:28.868
Your call is to fish.

01:36:29.201 --> 01:36:30.286
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

01:36:30.411 --> 01:36:32.872
Aye, for men.

01:36:36.208 --> 01:36:38.294
How can I do anything else now?

01:36:41.672 --> 01:36:43.549
Will you fish, too, Clavius?

01:36:51.432 --> 01:36:52.641
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:36:53.893 --> 01:36:55.227
Then,

01:36:55.895 --> 01:36:57.354
farewell, brother.

01:36:59.398 --> 01:37:00.733
Farewell.

01:37:04.361 --> 01:37:06.197
God bless and keep you.

01:37:15.831 --> 01:37:17.583
I will always have you with me.

01:37:21.587 --> 01:37:23.547
Always. <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)</font>

01:37:29.512 --> 01:37:32.097
<font color="#808080">APOSTLE:</font> Peter, come!

01:37:32.181 --> 01:37:34.934
Brothers! <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

01:37:35.476 --> 01:37:36.644
<font color="#808080">APOSTLE:</font> Peter!

01:37:36.727 --> 01:37:37.895
Brother!

01:37:38.646 --> 01:37:39.772
Wait!

01:37:48.447 --> 01:37:49.907
<font color="#808080">JAMES:</font> That way?

01:38:31.991 --> 01:38:34.660
I doubt we'll ever hear from them again.

01:38:46.589 --> 01:38:47.923
Tribune?

01:38:57.891 --> 01:38:59.810
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAVIUS INHALES QUIETLY)</font>

01:39:07.067 --> 01:39:08.444
My payment.

01:39:11.071 --> 01:39:12.197
Tribune,

01:39:15.117 --> 01:39:17.369
do you truly believe all this?

01:39:24.627 --> 01:39:25.878
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFTLY)</font> I believe...

01:39:28.297 --> 01:39:30.341
I can never be the same.

